[
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there a name in mathlib for the Type of sets containing a given set?</p>",
        "id": 211527134,
        "sender_full_name": "Thomas Browning",
        "timestamp": 1601315986
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You could use Icc but there might be a better way.</p>",
        "id": 211527255,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1601316025
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Something like this could work:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">variables</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">α</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">s</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">set</span> <span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">def</span> <span class=\"n\">subset</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">t</span> <span class=\"bp\">//</span> <span class=\"n\">s</span> <span class=\"bp\">⊆</span> <span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 211527386,
        "sender_full_name": "Pedro Minicz",
        "timestamp": 1601316080
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right -- the question is whether it's already there (in which case it might have an API)</p>",
        "id": 211527430,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1601316099
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What do you want to do with it?</p>",
        "id": 211527456,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1601316111
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>establish a galois connection between (subsets of L containing K) and (intermediate fields of L/K)</p>",
        "id": 211527535,
        "sender_full_name": "Thomas Browning",
        "timestamp": 1601316135
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>actually, it's possible that I don't need to insist that the subset contains K in order for this to work</p>",
        "id": 211527810,
        "sender_full_name": "Thomas Browning",
        "timestamp": 1601316295
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If you just use subsets is it not a Galois connection?</p>",
        "id": 211527821,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1601316300
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah, what you said</p>",
        "id": 211527843,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1601316314
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think you don't need to include \"containing K\" to get a Galois connection, yeah</p>",
